<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title><%= title %></title>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="<%= root %>favicon.ico">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="<%= root %>css/index.css">
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1><b><%= title %></b></h1>

        <p>
            This is a simple flag counter thingy I made by reusing code my guestbook,
            I have also merged some code from <a href="https://github.com/journey-ad/Moe-Counter">moe-counter</a>
            and added it in this repository because they way moe-counter works is simple +1 each request instead of
            saving IPs and counting unique requests.
        </p>

        <h2>Flag Counter</h2>
        <p>The original project.</p>

        <code>&lt;iframe frameborder="0" style="border: none; background: none; width: 100%; height: 180px; overflow: hidden;" scrolling="no" src="<%= root %>flags"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
        </code>
        
        <br><br>

        <div class="flag-counter">
            <iframe
                frameborder="0"
                style="border: none; background: none; width: 100%; height: 180px; overflow: hidden;"
                scrolling="no"
                src="<%= root %>flags"
            >
                Fun fact: Your browser sucks. (and you know it does)
            </iframe>
        </div>
        
        <h2>Moe Counter</h2>
        
        <p><code>&lt;img src="<%= root %>counter"&gt;</code></p>
        <img src="counter">

        <p>Add <code>&demo=true</code> for demo and <code>&digits=7</code> for something like: <code>0000092</code></p> and <code>theme=gelbooru</code> for the gelbooru theme</p>

        <img src="counter?demo=true&theme=gelbooru">
        <p><b>gelbooru</b></p>
        <img src="counter?demo=true&theme=asoul">
        <p><b>aosul</b></p>
        <img src="counter?demo=true&theme=moebooru">
        <p><b>moebooru</b></p>
    </body>
</html>
